# Rasm Rhino UI

Read `libs/csharp/Rasm.Rhino/AGENTS.md`, `libs/csharp/Rasm.Grasshopper/AGENTS.md`, and local RhinoWIP/GH2/Eto API truth before UI edits.

## Mac UI Invariants

- Parent Eto UI to the document window on macOS, using current Rhino UI evidence such as `RhinoEtoApp.MainWindowForDocument` when applicable.
- Marshal UI work through the existing UI rail; do not bypass `RhinoUi.Use`, `GhUi`, or `GrasshopperUi.Use`.
- Use the supplied command, UI, or document context; do not fall back to `RhinoDoc.ActiveDoc` when a document is available.
- Keep CADisplayLink, AppKit, and other native Mac details behind UI rails.

## Boundaries

- Rhino UI owns dialogs, panels, overlays, callbacks, progress, and UI-thread protection.
- GH UI owns canvas, document, editor, input, events, layout, paint, wire, undo, repaint, and snapshot policy.
- Do not introduce WinForms, WPF, polling loops, or a second Eto abstraction layer.

## Validation

Use static C# first. Add bridge verification when behavior depends on live RhinoWIP, GH2 canvas, Eto parenting, or UI-thread execution.
